(244, 1, '2024-10-21 22:30:43', '2024-10-21 22:30:43', '<!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"https://wbcmuaythai.com.mx/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/young-woman-boxer-training-gym-scaled-1-1024x682.jpg\",\"id\":235,\"dimRatio\":50,\"minHeight\":493,\"minHeightUnit\":\"px\",\"contentPosition\":\"center center\",\"align\":\"full\",\"style\":{\"color\":{\"duotone\":[\"rgb(19,54,40)\",\"#ffffff\"]}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull\" style=\"min-height:493px\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim\"></span><img class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-235\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://wbcmuaythai.com.mx/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/young-woman-boxer-training-gym-scaled-1-1024x682.jpg\" data-object-fit=\"cover\"/><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"large\",\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\",\"customFontSize\":100,\"lineHeight\":3,\"letterSpacing\":3,\"fontWeight\":\"900\",\"textTransform\":\"uppercase\",\"noBottomSpacing\":true,\"noTopSpacing\":true} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-large-font-size has-custom-font has-custom-weight has-custom-transform has-custom-lineheight has-custom-letterspacing mb-0 pb-0 mt-0 pt-0\" style=\"font-family:Rubik;line-height:3;letter-spacing:3px;font-weight:900;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:100px\"><span class=\"uppercase\"><strong>rules &amp; regulations</strong></span></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":6,\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<h6 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong><u>SECTION 1</u></strong></h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<h6 class=\"wp-block-heading has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">RULES AND REGULATIONS FOR MUAY THAI COMPETITIONS</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE 1: THE RING</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">&nbsp;1.1) The boxing ring must be equipped with an approved safety mat. It shall measure no less than 18 feet (5.5 meters) nor more than 24 feet (7.3 meters) square between the ropes unless mutually agreed to by both camps and authorized by the local combat sports commission and the WBC MuayThai supervisor. The apron shall extend 24 inches (0.61 meters) beyond the ropes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">1.2) The ring must have four (4) ropes for safety. The ropes may extend as high as 4 feet (1.22 meters)from the canvas and shall not be less than 1 inch (2.54 cm) in diameter, wrapped securely in a soft material and hung to a normal tightness.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">1.3) The ring shall have two (2) easily accessible stairways for the boxers and personnel to walk in and out safely and steps available for medical personnel to enter the ring. All four (4) corners must be covered with corner pads to protect the boxers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">1.4) All WBC MuayThai championship title contests must only be contested in a ring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;2:&nbsp;GLOVES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">2.1)&nbsp;The gloves for the fight will be 8 ounces from minimumweight up to including welterweight and 10 ounces from super welterweight up to including heavyweight. The promoter will provide gloves unless otherwise stated and agreed upon by all parties. After the gloves are chosen at the weigh-in, they shall remain in possession of either the supervisor or the local combat sports representative until they are delivered to the appropriate camps in the locker rooms. The spare gloves shall remain ringside with the WBC MuayThai supervisor or local combat sports commission representative. Any illegal manipulation of the gloves to provide an unfair advantage for a fighter shall cause sanctions against the appropriate camp as determined by the WBC MuayThai, and the auxiliary pair of gloves shall be used as the primary pair.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;3:&nbsp;HAND&nbsp;BANDAGES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">3.1) Fighters must wrap their hands with soft hand bandages not longer&nbsp;than six (6) meters and not wider than five (5) centimeters for each hand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">3.2) Fighters may use commission or sanctioning body-approved tape, but&nbsp;not longer than two and a half (2 ½) meters and two and a half (2 ½) centimeters wide for&nbsp;each hand to top-up on the wrist or bake of the hand. It is forbidden to top-up the&nbsp;tape across the knuckles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">3.3) Fighters must use only the bandages provided by the local combat sports commission, and the promoter may supply their own once checked by the commission’s team and/or the WBC MuayThai supervisor.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Hand wrapping must be inspected and stamped by the WBC fight supervisor or the local commission representative to certify that the wraps have been relatively placed on the hands of the&nbsp;fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;4:&nbsp;Dress Code</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.1) Fighters must wear shorts neatly at half-thigh length, without a shirt or shoes. A fighter’s shorts must not be the same color as the other corner. Shorts should preferably be the same as or close to the corner representing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.2) Fighters must wear groin protection for the genital organs made of solid material that protects them from knee or other blows. The use of the groin guard is mandatory<strong>.&nbsp;</strong>A metal groin protector and a jock strap may also be worn for male fighters<strong>.&nbsp;</strong>For female fighters, a female groin protector shall be worn</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.3) Fighter’s fingernails and toenails must be closely and neatly cut.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.4) Fighters shall wear a headband (Mongkon) only when they pay homage (Wai Kru/Ram Muay) before the bout. During the bout, fighters may wear an inscribed cloth, amulet, or charm around the upper arm (Prajiad). If the amulet interferes with the flow of the bout, it must be removed immediately by the referee or corner.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.5) Fighters may wear ankle supports, one for each ankle, but not to be shin supports or to roll halfway down. Wrapping the ankles and legs with pieces of cloth is not permitted. Ankle guards are not to be padded and may only be made of cloth. Nothing is to be worn under the ankle guards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.6) Fighters may strap an ankle for support if the strapping does not protrude outside an ankle guard and does not provide padding for contact, only support for hyperextension or rolling. Any strapping of ankles must be approved by the appointed WBC MuayThai supervisor at the same time as hand wraps are inspected. Strapping must not give an advantage to the athlete for impact. Fighters cannot wear belts, jewelry, or any dangerous ornaments as determined by the WBC MuayThai supervisor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.7) Liniment is allowed on the fighters body (below the neck) during pre fight massage only – and must be cleaned off before the fight, especially when, dripping, or running. Vaseline can be used in minimal quantities to limit cuts. Vaseline or liniment cannot be used on any attire. Gloves must be free of any liniment or related products, and the referee must check gloves before the start of each round.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">4.8) Form-fitted gum shields must be worn during the contest. It is forbidden for a fighter to spit out their gum shield during the contest intentionally. If the fighter does so, the fighter will be warned or disqualified for continuous infractions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<ul style=\"font-family:Rubik\" class=\"wp-block-list has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>RULE 5: WEIGHT DIVISIONS AND WEIGH-IN:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Divisions and weight limits for competitions</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Division                         Weight limits<!-- wp:list {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<ul style=\"font-family:Rubik\" class=\"wp-block-list has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li> Minimum weight 100 pounds (45.359 kg) <strong>**Female Only</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Mini-Flyweight: 105 pounds (47.627 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Light-Flyweight: 108 pounds (48.987)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Flyweight: 112 pounds (50.802 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Super-Flyweight: 115 pounds (52.163 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bantamweight: 118 pounds (53.524 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Super-Bantamweight: 122 pounds (55.338 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Featherweight: 126 pounds (57.153 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Super-Featherweight: 130 pounds (58.967 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Lightweight: 135 pounds (61.235 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Super Lightweight: 140 pounds (63.503 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Welterweight: 147 pounds (66.678 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Super-Welterweight: 154 pounds (69.853 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Middleweight: 160 pounds (72.575 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Super Middleweight: 168 pounds (76. 204. kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Light Heavyweight: 175 pounds (79.379 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Cruiserweight: 200 pounds (90.718 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Heavyweight: +200 pounds (+90.718 kg)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Weigh-in</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">5.1) Fighters must weigh in without clothes (underwear permitted) one day before the contest, 24-30 hours before the scheduled flight time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">5.2) Exceptions are made to the above rule when championships are held in&nbsp;Thailand&nbsp;following&nbsp;rules&nbsp;and regulations of the Boxing Board of Control and other certain circumstances with the agreement&nbsp;of the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;MuayThai supervisor&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;same-day&nbsp;weigh-in.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">5.3) Before the weigh-in, fighters must have their physical&nbsp;condition&nbsp;examination&nbsp;checked&nbsp;by the event doctor to certify that they are physically fit and healthy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">5.4) Female fighters must be allowed to weigh in private. Weigh-ins should only be conducted by female officials/witnesses.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">5.5) Safety&nbsp;Weigh-Ins.&nbsp;The&nbsp;final&nbsp;and&nbsp;official&nbsp;weigh-in&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;shall&nbsp;occur&nbsp;no&nbsp;less&nbsp;than&nbsp;24&nbsp;hours but&nbsp;not&nbsp;more&nbsp;than 30&nbsp;hours&nbsp;before&nbsp;a&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;MuayThai&nbsp;bout&nbsp;due&nbsp;to the&nbsp;possible&nbsp;adverse&nbsp;results&nbsp;of&nbsp;dehydration&nbsp;and&nbsp;subsequent&nbsp;rehydration&nbsp;of&nbsp;boxers&nbsp;to&nbsp;make&nbsp;the&nbsp;required&nbsp;weight&nbsp;limit&nbsp;for&nbsp;a bout.&nbsp;Further,&nbsp;to&nbsp;encourage&nbsp;safe&nbsp;weight&nbsp;loss&nbsp;in&nbsp;advance&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;MuayThai&nbsp;bout,&nbsp;additional pre-fight weigh-ins&nbsp;are&nbsp;to be&nbsp;held 30 and&nbsp;7&nbsp;days&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;official&nbsp;30-24-hour&nbsp;weigh-in&nbsp;for&nbsp;non-heavyweight&nbsp;boxers.&nbsp;The&nbsp;boxers’&nbsp;weight&nbsp;should&nbsp;be&nbsp;as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<ol style=\"font-family:Rubik\" class=\"wp-block-list has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>30-day weigh-in: 30 days before the bout, the boxers’ weight should not exceed 10% of the weight limit for the bout;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>14-day weigh-in: 14-days before the bout, the boxers’ weight should not exceed 5% of the weight limit for the bout</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>7-day weigh-in: 7 days before the bout, the boxers’ weight should not exceed 3% of the weight limit for the bout. Fighters and their representatives, managers, trainers, and promoters, and not the WBC MuayThai, are solely responsible for arranging the pre-bout safety weigh-ins and medical examinations and tests required by this rule. Failure on the part of those parties to comply with the above guidelines may result in the WBC MuayThai taking such actions as it deems appropriate in its sole discretion, revocation of challenger status and opportunities, or vacating a title. If a fighter exceeds any weight limitation stated above (above an unsatisfactory amount) the WBC MuayThai may, for the safety of the fighter or their opponent, revoke or deny its sanction of the bout. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">5.6) A fighter who misses championship weight on the scales is disqualified from winning a title. The fight can continue however a fighter should be more than 2.2 kgs (5 pounds) over the championship weight division for the safety of the opponent who made weight and can still win the title.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">All parties must be in agreement for the contest to continue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE 6: PAYING HOMAGE</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">6.1) Paying Homage: Before the bout, every fighter should pay homage to the&nbsp;ancient arts and customs of MuayThai, accompanied by Thai musical instruments of a&nbsp;Javanese oboe, a Javanese tom-tom (drum), and a pair of small cup-shaped cymbals for&nbsp;rhythms. The bout will start after paying homage, and at a minimum, both fighters seal the ring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The performing of the Wai Kru/Ram is not religious but rather a cultural art forms unique to the sport and culture of MuayThai.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE 7: ROUNDS</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">7.1) Rounds for competition: A professional WBC MuayThai championship bout consists of&nbsp;five (5) rounds of three (3) minutes each with two (2) minutes rest periods between rounds.&nbsp;Female bouts consist of five (5) rounds of two (2)minutes each with two (2) minutes resting&nbsp;period between rounds with the resting period between rounds belonging to the previous round.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">*WBC MuayThai professional female world championship fights may be contested over three (3) minute rounds with the agreement of the local Combat Sports Commission, both fighter’s camps, and the WBC MuayThai appointed supervisor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;8:&nbsp;FIGHTER’S&nbsp;QUALIFICATIONS&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">8.1) The minimum age to complete a WBC MuayThai professional title is 18-years old outside of the Kingdom of Thailand and under the Sports Authority of Thailand rules under its Boxing Board of Control the minimum age in Thailand is 16 years old and the fighter must be fully registered in Thailand with an up to date boxer’s book.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">8.2) Elite Thai stadium champions who are currently not ranked may qualify to compete for vacant WBC MuayThai world titles under special circumstances as per the final ratification of the WBC MuayThai world championship executive committee.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;9:&nbsp;SECONDS</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.1) A fighter may have three (3), seconds, but only two (2) seconds are allowed into the ring&nbsp;during&nbsp;a round interval with the chief second identified in the WBC MuayThai rules meeting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;Seconds&nbsp;Duties:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.2) The seconds are allowed to give verbal advice only, from a safe distance, during the&nbsp;fight, if&nbsp;they violate the rule, the referee will warn, caution, or discharge them their duties.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.3) During&nbsp;the bout,&nbsp;the&nbsp;seconds&nbsp;must&nbsp;stay&nbsp;on&nbsp;their&nbsp;seats. Before&nbsp;each&nbsp;round,&nbsp;they&nbsp;must&nbsp;clear&nbsp;towels,&nbsp;water&nbsp;bottles, and&nbsp;other&nbsp;materials&nbsp;from&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;edge.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.4) During a round interval, the second must check the fighter’s gloves, shorts, or any other&nbsp;relevant items, if there are any problems, the chief second must notify the referee immediately to solve them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.5) Seconds&nbsp;shall not use rude&nbsp;words&nbsp;and&nbsp;they&nbsp;shall not hurt&nbsp;(physically)&nbsp;the fighters&nbsp;during&nbsp;the bout, or after.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.6) Seconds must wear a corner jacket/vest,&nbsp;with no rude words or rude symbols on the corner jackets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.7) Seconds&nbsp;may&nbsp;arrange&nbsp;their&nbsp;own material, equipment,&nbsp;and&nbsp;medical&nbsp;supplies&nbsp;at their&nbsp;corners as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Water</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Ice</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Towels</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The adrenaline&nbsp;of&nbsp;1/1000&nbsp;solution&nbsp;or&nbsp;other&nbsp;substances&nbsp;as&nbsp;approved&nbsp;ring&nbsp;doctor</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Gauze</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Cotton&nbsp;buds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A&nbsp;pair&nbsp;of&nbsp;safety&nbsp;scissors</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Wound&nbsp;bandages</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Absorbent&nbsp;cotton&nbsp;bandages&nbsp;or&nbsp;wound&nbsp;soft&nbsp;bandages</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">9.8) Fighter’s chief second may look to pull their fighter from a fight to protect their safety by stepping up onto the ring&nbsp;apron to grab the attention of the referee. He/she is not allowed to throw a sponge or a towel into the ring. And the final decision to call off a bout will rest with the referee who may consult with the ringside doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;10:&nbsp;REFEREES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">10.1) The referees&nbsp;must&nbsp;wear blue or black trousers, a light green shirt or black polo&nbsp;shirt&nbsp;with&nbsp;official&nbsp;WBCMuayThai&nbsp;logo&nbsp;on&nbsp;the left-hand&nbsp;side&nbsp;pocket,&nbsp;and&nbsp;wear&nbsp;lightweight&nbsp;boots&nbsp;or a WBC branded polo shirt. They shall not wear eyeglasses or metal ornaments. Their fingernails&nbsp;must be neatly cut.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">10.2) The&nbsp;Referee’s&nbsp;duties:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;referee’s&nbsp;main priority&nbsp;is&nbsp;safeguarding and protecting&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;from&nbsp;undue injuries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;always&nbsp;uphold&nbsp;rules&nbsp;and&nbsp;justice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;closely&nbsp;control&nbsp;the&nbsp;bout at&nbsp;all&nbsp;times with a duty of care for both fighters as his/her priority.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;inspect&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighter’s&nbsp;gloves,&nbsp;dresses,&nbsp;and&nbsp;gum&nbsp;shields.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;use&nbsp;three&nbsp;commands&nbsp;as&nbsp;follows.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">“หยุด”&nbsp;(YUD):&nbsp;To&nbsp;order&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;to&nbsp;stop.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">“แยก”&nbsp;(YAK): To order the fighter to separate from each other. After the “แยก”&nbsp;command, both fighters must step back at least one step before engaging in the fight&nbsp;again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">“ชก”&nbsp;(CHOK):&nbsp;To&nbsp;order&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;to&nbsp;fight.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must utter&nbsp;strong&nbsp;verbal&nbsp;utterances&nbsp;to&nbsp;offending fighters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The referee shall not allow a fighter who intentionally violates rules to gain an advantage, e.g., grabbing ropes to kick or knee his opponent, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The referee shall not engage in any action which may jeopardize the fighters who&nbsp;may&nbsp;gain&nbsp;or&nbsp;lose&nbsp;advantages,&nbsp;e.g.,fast-slow&nbsp;counting,&nbsp;warning&nbsp;or&nbsp;no&nbsp;warning,&nbsp;etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">At the end of each round, the referee must collect the scorecards from the three&nbsp;judges. After&nbsp;that, he/she&nbsp;will&nbsp;hand&nbsp;all score&nbsp;cards&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;MuayThai&nbsp;supervisor&nbsp;for&nbsp;tabulation&nbsp;on&nbsp;the scoring master sheet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The referee shall neither criticize nor give an interview about the future fights or&nbsp;the&nbsp;past&nbsp;fight&nbsp;results&nbsp;unless&nbsp;he&nbsp;gets permission&nbsp;from&nbsp;Chairman&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;officials.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;Referee’s&nbsp;Power:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To stop the contest when seeing that one boxer is outclassing the other to the&nbsp;extent that there is a risk to the health and safety of a fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To stop the contest when seeing that the fighter is too seriously injured to&nbsp;continue to bout. He/she may consult with the ring doctor for professional consolation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To&nbsp;stop&nbsp;the&nbsp;contest&nbsp;when&nbsp;seeing&nbsp;that&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;intentionally&nbsp;disrupting&nbsp;the&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;case,&nbsp;either&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;or&nbsp;both&nbsp;may be&nbsp;disqualified.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To stop the counting when seeing that if he continues the count, the fighter&nbsp;may be in danger.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To stop the count when the opponent has not gone to the furthest neutral corner before the count is finished.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To stop the action to warn or caution the fighter to violate rules or for other reasons to restore justice or enforce rules.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To disqualify the fighter who ignores the referee’s commands, who physically harms the&nbsp;referee, or who aggressively offends the referee.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">&nbsp;To discharge from duty, the second who disobeys&nbsp;the referee may disqualify the fighter whose second disobeys the referee’s orders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">For the fighter who severely violates rules, the referee has the power to disqualify him, or he may declare the bout “no decision” after warning or cautioning, or ever without&nbsp;any previous warning or cautioning.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To caution the fighter who violates the rules, the referee must stop the action before he/she cautions the offended boxer so that the fighter understands the cause&nbsp;and objective of the referee must show a hand signal, pointing to the fighter to inform all&nbsp;judges that there is a caution. The referee must disqualify the fighter who has been given three&nbsp;cautions or declare “no decision” if it is a serious offense, the referee may disqualify him even&nbsp;though there is no previous caution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Counting&nbsp;procedure&nbsp;for&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;outside&nbsp;the&nbsp;stage.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When a fighter&nbsp;has been attacked by his opponent’s legal weapons, and as a result, the fighter&nbsp;falls&nbsp;off&nbsp;outside&nbsp;the stage,&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;order&nbsp;his&nbsp;opponent&nbsp;to&nbsp;go&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;furthest&nbsp;neutral&nbsp;If the boxer outside the stage is too slow to get into the stage, the referee shall count immediately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">For&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;falling&nbsp;outside&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring,&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;shall&nbsp;count&nbsp;to&nbsp;“ยสบ”&nbsp;(YISIP)&nbsp;or&nbsp;twenty&nbsp;(20).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;a&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;or&nbsp;both&nbsp;falls&nbsp;off&nbsp;outside&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring,&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;shall count to&nbsp;“ยสบ”&nbsp;(20).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">If the fighter&nbsp;manages to get into the ring before the count of twenty, the bout will continue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When a fighter falls off outside the ring, the referee shall stop continue if the fighter is&nbsp;obstructed or delayed going up into the ring by any person. The referee shall clearly warn the offender&nbsp;and&nbsp;continue&nbsp;the&nbsp;count.&nbsp;If the&nbsp;offender disobeys,&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;shall&nbsp;stop&nbsp;the&nbsp;bout&nbsp;and disqualify a fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When both fighters fall off outside the ring, the referee shall count. If either boxer tries to delay the action, the referee shall stop counting and clearly warns the After that, the referee will continue the count. If the offender disobeys, the referee shall disqualify that boxer to lose&nbsp;the fight or of “No Decision.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">If both fighters fall off outside the ring, the referee shall When a fighter can get back into the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;count&nbsp;of twenty, the&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;the&nbsp;winner.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">However,&nbsp;if&nbsp;both fighters&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;get&nbsp;back&nbsp;into&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;count&nbsp;of&nbsp;“ยสบ”&nbsp;twenty,&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;shall&nbsp;declare&nbsp;a&nbsp;draw.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;11:&nbsp;JUDGES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">11.1) Judges must dress the same as the referees. They may wear eyeglasses when performing their&nbsp;duties. The judge’s duties are as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">11.2) Each judge must sit next to the ring on three sides with no one impeding&nbsp;their view. During the bout, the judges shall not speak with anyone. If necessary, they may speak with the WBC&nbsp;MuayThai appointed supervisor during the resting interval of rounds to inform them that&nbsp;there have been some incidents e.g., the second’s misconduct and losing of ropes, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">11.3) Judges must score the bout objectively, with clear and independent thought, and score according to the rules. They must record scores on the score cards immediately after each&nbsp;They must sign the score cards before handing them to the referee.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">11.4) Judges&nbsp;shall&nbsp;not&nbsp;leave&nbsp;their&nbsp;seats&nbsp;until&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring announcer&nbsp;declares&nbsp;the&nbsp;official&nbsp;result and the referee raises a winner’s hand or both for a draw.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">11.5) Judges shall neither criticize nor give an interview about fight results or the past fight&nbsp;results unless they get permission from the chairman of the ring officials.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;12:&nbsp;TIMEKEEPER</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.1) The&nbsp;timekeeper&nbsp;must&nbsp;sit&nbsp;beside&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;at&nbsp;delighted&nbsp;seats.&nbsp;Their&nbsp;duties&nbsp;are as follows</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.2) The&nbsp;timekeeper’s&nbsp;duties:&nbsp;To&nbsp;keep&nbsp;the&nbsp;number&nbsp;of&nbsp;rounds&nbsp;and&nbsp;fighting&nbsp;time&nbsp;for&nbsp;each&nbsp;round,&nbsp;resting interval time between rounds, and time of time-outs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.3) To&nbsp;signal&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;beginning&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;ending&nbsp;of&nbsp;round&nbsp;by&nbsp;striking&nbsp;the&nbsp;bell.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.4) To&nbsp;signal&nbsp;for&nbsp;five&nbsp;(5)&nbsp;seconds&nbsp;before&nbsp;beginning&nbsp;each&nbsp;round&nbsp;to&nbsp;clear&nbsp;the&nbsp;stage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.5) To&nbsp;deduct&nbsp;the&nbsp;interruption time&nbsp;or&nbsp;the&nbsp;time&nbsp;stopped&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee’s&nbsp;order.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.6) To&nbsp;always keep the correct time&nbsp;by&nbsp;stopwatch&nbsp;or&nbsp;clock.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">12.7) The timekeeper shall not give the bell signal while the referee is counting even&nbsp;though the fighting time of that round The timekeeper will strike the bell when the referee order “ชก”&nbsp;(CHOK).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;13:&nbsp;DECISIONS</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Winning&nbsp;by&nbsp;Points</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;the&nbsp;bout&nbsp;ends,&nbsp;there&nbsp;are&nbsp;three&nbsp;possible&nbsp;outcomes&nbsp;for&nbsp;winning&nbsp;on&nbsp;points.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Unanimous&nbsp;Decision&nbsp;(UPD),&nbsp;all&nbsp;3&nbsp;judges&nbsp;favor&nbsp;the&nbsp;same&nbsp;fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Split&nbsp;Decision&nbsp;(SPD)&nbsp;2&nbsp;judges&nbsp;favor&nbsp;one&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;judge&nbsp;favors&nbsp;the&nbsp;other&nbsp;fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Majority&nbsp;Decision&nbsp;(MPD)&nbsp;2&nbsp;judges&nbsp;favor&nbsp;one&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;judge&nbsp;scores&nbsp;a&nbsp;draw.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Winning&nbsp;by&nbsp;Knockout&nbsp;(KO)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">If the&nbsp;fighter is&nbsp;knocked&nbsp;down and&nbsp;cannot continue&nbsp;the&nbsp;fight after&nbsp;ten&nbsp;(10) seconds,&nbsp;their opponent will win by knockout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Winning&nbsp;by&nbsp;Technical&nbsp;Knockout&nbsp;(TKO)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;wins&nbsp;the&nbsp;contest&nbsp;by&nbsp;technical&nbsp;knockout&nbsp;in&nbsp;such&nbsp;conditions&nbsp;as&nbsp;follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;a&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;outclasses&nbsp;their&nbsp;opponent&nbsp;very&nbsp;clearly&nbsp;or&nbsp;one-sided&nbsp;out-points their&nbsp;opponent in such conditions that his opponent may be seriously injured.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When his/her opponent cannot continue the contest immediately after the resting interval of a round.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;his/her&nbsp;opponent&nbsp;is&nbsp;so&nbsp;seriously&nbsp;injured&nbsp;that&nbsp;he&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;continue&nbsp;the&nbsp;contest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;his/her&nbsp;opponent&nbsp;has&nbsp;been&nbsp;counted&nbsp;for&nbsp;more&nbsp;than&nbsp;two&nbsp;(2)&nbsp;times&nbsp;(=3&nbsp;times) in one round or more than four (4) times (=5 times) all though in the span of the contest since the first&nbsp;round.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;his&nbsp;opponent&nbsp;has&nbsp;fallen&nbsp;out&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;and&nbsp;he&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;get&nbsp;back&nbsp;into&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;after&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;has&nbsp;counted&nbsp;“ยสบ”&nbsp;(YISIP)&nbsp;or&nbsp;twenty&nbsp;(20)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">His/her&nbsp;opponent&nbsp;willfully&nbsp;withdraws&nbsp;from&nbsp;the&nbsp;contest because&nbsp;of injury&nbsp;or&nbsp;other causes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Winning&nbsp;by&nbsp;Disqualification&nbsp;of&nbsp;Opponent</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">No&nbsp;Titles&nbsp;Contests</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case a fighter does not pass the ring doctor’s physical examination, or they do not make the division weight-in, or he/she&nbsp;does&nbsp;not show&nbsp;up&nbsp;to compete&nbsp;as&nbsp;scheduled, the&nbsp;title will&nbsp;be&nbsp;declared&nbsp;a “No Contest”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">*In a&nbsp;title contest when&nbsp;the champion cannot&nbsp;make&nbsp;weight&nbsp;or pass the&nbsp;physical examination&nbsp;or fails to show then his title will be declared vacant.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">*If&nbsp;the&nbsp;champion&nbsp;is&nbsp;overweight&nbsp;(he/she&nbsp;loses&nbsp;the&nbsp;title&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;scales)&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;two&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;agree&nbsp;to fight,&nbsp;and the champion&nbsp;is&nbsp;beaten,&nbsp;then the&nbsp;challenger will be declared&nbsp;the new champion.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">*If&nbsp;the&nbsp;challenger&nbsp;can’t&nbsp;make&nbsp;weight&nbsp;the&nbsp;event&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;declared&nbsp;a&nbsp;no&nbsp;contest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">&nbsp;A&nbsp;Draw&nbsp;Decision</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">&nbsp;A&nbsp;contest&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;decided&nbsp;as&nbsp;a&nbsp;draw&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;following&nbsp;condition:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">There&nbsp;are&nbsp;three&nbsp;possible&nbsp;scoring&nbsp;decisions&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;drawn&nbsp;contest:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Unanimous&nbsp;Draw&nbsp;(UD)&nbsp;All&nbsp;3&nbsp;judges&nbsp;score&nbsp;the&nbsp;contest&nbsp;a&nbsp;draw</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Majority&nbsp;Draw&nbsp;(MD)&nbsp;2&nbsp;judges&nbsp;score&nbsp;it&nbsp;a&nbsp;draw,&nbsp;and&nbsp;1&nbsp;judge&nbsp;has&nbsp;a&nbsp;winner</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Split&nbsp;Draw&nbsp;(SD)&nbsp;judge&nbsp;scores&nbsp;it&nbsp;a&nbsp;draw&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;other&nbsp;2&nbsp;judges&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;different&nbsp;winner.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;both&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;are&nbsp;knocked&nbsp;down,&nbsp;and&nbsp;they&nbsp;have&nbsp;been&nbsp;counted&nbsp;out&nbsp;of&nbsp;“สบ”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(SIP)&nbsp;or&nbsp;ten&nbsp;(10).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;both&nbsp;boxers&nbsp;have&nbsp;fallen&nbsp;out of&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring,&nbsp;they&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;continue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">No&nbsp;Decision</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When the referee considers that either boxer or both “fight dishonorably,” he declares that&nbsp;“There is no decision for this bout as the red corner / blue corner / or both fighters fight dishonorably”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">No&nbsp;Contests</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case the fighters intentionally spoil the fight and they have been warned and cautioned by the referee, but they keep on spoiling the fight, the referee shall stop the contest and shall&nbsp;declare “No contest for his bout.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Cancellation&nbsp;of&nbsp;Contest</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case of the ring damage, a riot from spectators, or an unexpected situation causing it impossible to continue the contest, the referee shall cancel the contest and declares “Cancellation of the contest.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Vacated&nbsp;Titles</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">If a current WBC MuayThai champion fights in any professional MuayThai contest, in or under his/her&nbsp;championship title weight category, and loses by KO or TKO in such contest, his/her WBC&nbsp;MuayThai title will be&nbsp;declared vacant. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;14:&nbsp;SCORING&nbsp;PROCEDURES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Competent&nbsp;scoring&nbsp;must&nbsp;be&nbsp;done&nbsp;using&nbsp;the&nbsp;following&nbsp;criteria:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When the fighter uses their fists, feet, knees, and elbows as effective and controlled&nbsp;MuayThai fighting weapons to attack their opponent powerfully, accurately, and according to the&nbsp;rules with effective and powerful techniques scoring higher than less effective strikes. The effective execution of any weapon will score higher than a less effective/timid execution of&nbsp;another weapon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">&nbsp;Scoring&nbsp;Procedures</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Fighters who can do more damage to their opponent using all MuayThai fighting weapons effectively, with heavier, powerful, and accurate attacks on their opponent, using&nbsp;clear, effective aggression with their offensive skills (damage), ring-craft skills (dominance), and&nbsp;defensive skills (disruption) by MuayThai arts and techniques, all contribute to a boxer&nbsp;winning the round – with extra credibility leaning towards the effective execution of attacking&nbsp;techniques.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;Ten&nbsp;Point&nbsp;Must&nbsp;System&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Scoring&nbsp;Explained</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The winner of a round must have 10 points</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The loser of a round will get 9, 8, 7, or a low of 6, depending on various factors in the round.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">If there is no clear winner, both fighters will get 10 points – if in doubt – score it even point deductions by a referee for fouls in a championship fight are cumulated on the supervisor’s master sheet</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-10 score shall be given when a judge’s mental computation at the end of the round is not clear enough to give a highly questionable round to either fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Just because you have been instructed against scoring even rounds, it would be unfair to a fighter to score a round in favor of the other fighter if your mental computer witnessed no difference.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-9 score shall be given in a round with a slight advantage in overall action favoring one fighter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-9 &nbsp;score shall be given, also, when there is a clear advantage but not an overwhelming advantage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-8 score shall be given when there is a knockdown, and the rest of the round is a very slight advantage for the fighter who scored the knockdown</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-8 score shall be given when there is an overwhelming one-sided round; even without a knockdown, a real beating by one of the fighters over the other shall be always a 10-8 round</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-9 score shall be given to fighter A when fighter B takes an eight-count, but B clearly and unquestionably wins the rest of the round, before and after the knockdown</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-10 score shall be given when a knocked down fighter gets up and then knocks down his rival with the rest of the round, somehow even</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-9 score should be given when both fighters are knocked down – but one of them wins the rest of the round</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A 10-7 score shall be given on two knockdowns of the same fighter – but always consider what happened before and the knockdowns</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">No round should be scored lower than 10-6</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Make sure that your scorecard is accurate and reflects your decision on each round before handing the card to the referee</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">At the start of each round, a judge will set his/her mental computer at the sound of the bell to 10-10, even or no advantage count</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When a judge’s mind is immersed – without any distraction to compute even scoring – and sees no difference in the action of the fighters precisely at the end of the round – this is a 10-10 round</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Your competent mental computing has one of the fighters slightly ahead of the other based on what you witnessed over the entire round. As we do not want many even rounds, a slight advantage should be a 10-9 round (Close)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">&nbsp;Your computing of the actions leads you to have one of the fighters ahead after completing the entire round. This is also a 10-9 round (Moderate)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Your computing of the actions leads you to have one of the fighters winning the round by a large margin of victory. This is also a 10-9 round (Decisive)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Your mental count sees one fighter give a one-sided beating and hurt their opponent throughout the round – the only thing missing was a knockdown. This is a 10- 8 round – don’t fear being right (Extreme Decisive)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Clean and effective strikes: Landing punches, elbows, knees, or kicks to the scoring area of your opponent with power, volume, and accuracy to cause damage, domination, or disruption to your opponent</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Damage: If a fighter is trying to hurt their opponent, a judge should look for evidence of damage knocking your opponent down, staggering your opponent, significant blows that slow your opponent’s attacking prowess</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Domination: If a fighter is trying to control their opponent, a judge should look for evidence of domination, an overwhelming advantage in strikes landed repeated initiates action during exchanges repeatedly lands the last strike in exchanges</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Disruption: If a fighter is trying to prevent their opponent from hurting or controlling them, a judge should look for evidence of disruption, effective counter strikes that alter an opponent’s strategy that force an opponent to grab, and hold strikes that force an opponent into a defensive posture</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Effective Aggression: A forceful willingness to attack your opponent (either moving forward, backward or remaining stationary) where your strikes land accurately and force on your opponent. Remember, there is a fundamental difference between effective aggression and aggression</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Ring Generalship: Controlling the balance, pace, positioning, and style of the fight to a greater degree than that of your opponent</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Defense: Displaying successful evasive maneuvers to avoid being hit and showcasing defensive mechanisms as part of an offensive strategy to attack your opponent and negate their attacks</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Concentrate on your task over the entire fight</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<ul style=\"font-family:Rubik\" class=\"wp-block-list has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Treat each round separately</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Never look back at the previous round · Do not look forward to the next round</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Look for: Damage, Dominance, Disruption</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Evaluate: Effective Aggression, Ring Generalship &amp; Defense</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When scoring knockdowns, one knockdown in a round is not automatically a 10-8 round, two knockdowns in a round in not automatically a 10-7 round, and three knockdowns in a round are not automatically a 10-6 round; a judge must also take into consideration what happened in action before and after the knockdown (s)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Clinch scoring</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Scoring in the clinch</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(i) MuayThai technique must land on target with power</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(ii) MuayThai technique must be effective, or it is not scored</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(iii) MuayThai technique must not have a foul or follow a foul</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Clinch general</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(i) where scoring clinching techniques are applied by one or both fighters, the clinch will be allowed to run.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(ii) where both fighters are using a nonpowerful clinch technique, then the clinch will be stopped.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(iii) if both fighters are working for a dominant clinch position without any striking, the clinch will be allowed to run for a period if both fighters are working and not locking, holding, or being inactive.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(iv) if both fighters cannot work to a dominant clinch position, the clinch will be stopped immediately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(v) if one fighter applies for an effective lock position, for a period, the clinch is stopped.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(vi) if one fighter applies a successful defense technique where no more scoring techniques can be applied, the clinch is stopped.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;15:&nbsp;VIOLATIONS&nbsp;OF&nbsp;RULES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Biting,&nbsp;eye-poking,&nbsp;spitting&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;opponent,&nbsp;head&nbsp;butting&nbsp;or&nbsp;striking&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;groin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Back-breaking, using Judo throws and wrestling techniques.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Intentional&nbsp;rope&nbsp;grabbing&nbsp;to&nbsp;gain&nbsp;advantage&nbsp;over&nbsp;your&nbsp;opponent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Using&nbsp;provocative&nbsp;manners&nbsp;and&nbsp;words&nbsp;during&nbsp;contest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Disobeying&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee’s&nbsp;orders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Knee striking at the opponent’s protective cup, e.g., neck holding for knee striking at the&nbsp;protective cup, straight knee striking at the protective cup, or jumping knee striking at the&nbsp;protective cup. For these violations, the referee has the right to allow a resting time-out not more&nbsp;than five (5) minutes&nbsp;for the boxer who’s protective, the referee&nbsp;shall declare him/her&nbsp;as&nbsp;the loser or “no decision”.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Catching the opponent’s leg and pushing forwards more than two (2) steps without using any weapon. The referee shall order a fighter to stop and give a warning. After two warnings, the referee shall caution him.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">After kicking with his kicking leg being caught, the boxer pretends to throw himself down&nbsp;on ring floor. It is considered taking advantage of his/her opponent. The referee shall give&nbsp;him/her a warning. If the boxer repasts the action and the referee has given him/her two&nbsp;warnings; the referee shall caution him/her.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When&nbsp;both&nbsp;fighters&nbsp;fall&nbsp;out&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;ring&nbsp;and&nbsp;either&nbsp;boxer&nbsp;tries&nbsp;to&nbsp;delay&nbsp;the&nbsp;action.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Any&nbsp;strikes&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;back&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;head,&nbsp;neck,&nbsp;or&nbsp;spine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Deliberate&nbsp;kicks&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;groin&nbsp;area.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;16:&nbsp;KNOCKDOWNS</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A&nbsp;“knockdown&nbsp;means&nbsp;a&nbsp;situation&nbsp;when&nbsp;a&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;falls&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;canvas&nbsp;from&nbsp;a&nbsp;legal&nbsp;strike&nbsp;in which the referee must do a mandatory 8-count.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A fighter leans&nbsp;helplessly&nbsp;on the ring ropes or leans&nbsp;on&nbsp;the ring ropes, or he/she sits&nbsp;on the ring ropes caused by legal strikes in which the referee must either call the bout off or give the fighter a mandatory 8-count.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">After serious blows, he/she manages to withstand them without a fall, but in the condition that he/she cannot defend himself.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Procedure&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;knockdown</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case&nbsp;a fighter is attacked, and he/she is knocked down, the referee shall count at the same time he orders the opponent to go to the furthest neutral corner If the opponent disobeys this order, the referee must stop counting until that fighter goes to the furthest neutral corner. By then, he/she will continue to count the number next to the last counted one. When the knocked-down boxer stands up and is ready,&nbsp;“ชก”&nbsp;(CHOK).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case the knocked down fighter manages to stand up before the referee</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">counts&nbsp;out&nbsp;of&nbsp;“สบ”&nbsp;(SIP)&nbsp;or&nbsp;ten&nbsp;(10),&nbsp;and&nbsp;ready&nbsp;to&nbsp;continue,&nbsp;but&nbsp;his&nbsp;count&nbsp;is&nbsp;not&nbsp;yet&nbsp;“แปด”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(PAD)&nbsp;or&nbsp;eight&nbsp;(8),&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;continue&nbsp;counting&nbsp;until&nbsp;“แปด”&nbsp;(8)&nbsp;before&nbsp;he&nbsp;orders&nbsp;“ชก”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">(CHOK)&nbsp;to&nbsp;continue&nbsp;the&nbsp;bout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">If the knocked down fighter is ready to continue before the count of “สบ</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">”&nbsp;Or</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">ten&nbsp;(10),&nbsp;but he falls again without any additional attacks; the referee shall continue to&nbsp;count the number next to the last counted one.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In&nbsp;the&nbsp;knocked&nbsp;down&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;is&nbsp;ready&nbsp;to&nbsp;continue&nbsp;before&nbsp;“ส”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">”&nbsp;Or&nbsp;ten&nbsp;(10),&nbsp;it&nbsp;shall&nbsp;be&nbsp;considered&nbsp;that the&nbsp;contest is&nbsp;over,&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;shall&nbsp;declare that&nbsp;the&nbsp;knocked&nbsp;down&nbsp;fighter loses the bout “knockout.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case both fighters fall simultaneously, the referee shall keep on&nbsp;continue if there is still one boxer in the ring If both fighters cannot manage to stand</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">up&nbsp;until&nbsp;they&nbsp;are&nbsp;counted&nbsp;out&nbsp;of&nbsp;“สบ</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">”&nbsp;Or&nbsp;ten&nbsp;(10),&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;shall&nbsp;declare&nbsp;a&nbsp;“draw.”&nbsp;If&nbsp;both down fighters have their arms or legs tangled or one fighter is on top of the other but&nbsp;trying to stand up, the referee must stop the count and separate them. After that, he continues&nbsp;his count if there is still one fighter down on the ring floor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case of a knockdown, the referee must wait for one (1) second to pass by&nbsp;before he/she starts counting loudly from one to ten with a one-second interval. Along with his&nbsp;counting action, the referee must show a hand signal each second for that boxer&nbsp;to&nbsp;recognize the count.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In case there is one fighter not ready to continue the bout immediately after&nbsp;the resting interval between rounds, the referee&nbsp;must&nbsp;count unless&nbsp;due to improper&nbsp;dressing&nbsp;or&nbsp;the ring floor and stage are not in good condition for the contest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;17:&nbsp;HANDSHAKES &amp; RESPECT</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Both fighters&nbsp;shall&nbsp;shake&nbsp;hands&nbsp;before&nbsp;beginning&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;first-round&nbsp;contest&nbsp;and&nbsp;before&nbsp;beginning&nbsp;of the final&nbsp;round contest&nbsp;symbolizing that they&nbsp;will&nbsp;compete in the&nbsp;spirit of sportsmanship&nbsp;and in accordance with rules.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE&nbsp;18:&nbsp;RING&nbsp;DOCTOR</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The ring doctor’s duties: The ring doctor must be at a designated ringside seat throughout the&nbsp;contest until the last bout ends. The following are also the ring doctor’s duties:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To&nbsp;check&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighter’s&nbsp;physical&nbsp;examination&nbsp;before&nbsp;the&nbsp;weigh-in&nbsp;to&nbsp;certify&nbsp;that&nbsp;the&nbsp;fighter&nbsp;is physically fit and healthy, without any prohibited disease or sickness.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To&nbsp;give&nbsp;advice&nbsp;and&nbsp;suggestion&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;referee&nbsp;on&nbsp;request and to offer medical attention to fighters who may require immediate medical treatment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">To perform random anti-doping tests in accordance with VADA rules and the rules of the World Boxing Council MuayThai.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>RULE&nbsp;19:&nbsp;DRUGS&nbsp;OR&nbsp;PROHIBITED&nbsp;SUBSTANCES</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">It is prohibited to let a fighter use any drugs or chemical substances, which are not part of a fighter’s usual diet.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">It is possible to use a substance for local anesthesia, but only with the ring doctor’s approval.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A fighter who uses a prohibited substance, or the person who gives a fighter a prohibited substance, must be penalized by WBC MuayThai executive committee.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A fighter or an official who violates regulations of drugs or prohibited substances must be penalized and prohibited from any bout or participation in any MuayThai activities for a period decided by the WBC MuayThai Executive Committee.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":6,\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<h6 class=\"wp-block-heading has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Rule 20: Championship Defenses &amp; Appeals&nbsp;</h6>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>20.1 Timing of Defenses</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The WBC MuayThai’s policy is to offer opportunities to ranked fighters to compete for its titles. Thus the WBC MuayThai seeks to prevent titles from being frozen due to inactivity by champions. Therefore, where possible, a WBC MuayThai champion should strive to defend their title at least twice a year, with the following rules being strictly enforced unless otherwise authorized by the president of the WBC MuayThai.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>20.2 World Champions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>World champions are obligated to defend their titles within six months from the date of their first championship win or the date of their most recent championship defense. After the six-month period expires, a world champion will receive a further 60-day period of grace (at the sole discretion of The WBC MuayThai) to accommodate the champion to have a championship defense or for the champion or champion’s representative to notify the WBC MuayThai of a planned title defense. Upon or during the grace period of 60-days, should the WBC MuayThai not receive any communication from the champion or the champion’s representative to notify of a planned defense, the WBC MuayThai has the right to vacate the relevant champion of their world title without any prior written or oral notice. Suppose a champion or champion representative refuses a world title defense. In that case, The WBC MuayThai, in its sole discretion, has the right to immediately vacate a WBC MuayThai world champion of their status as world champion.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A world champion is entitled to petition the WBC MuayThai to have one voluntary defense after winning a world title where they can defend their title against a suitable opponent from the current top fifteen fighters in the world rankings of their division or a division below or above pending approval by the WBC MuayThai.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>20.3 International Champions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">International champions have six months from the day they win their title, to either defend their championship or notify the WBC MuayThai of a confirmed title defense (within a reasonable timeframe), failure to do so allows the WBC MuayThai to vacate the champion at any time thereafter the six-month period, without prior written or oral notification.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">It is the responsibility of a champion or champion representative to communicate to the WBC MuayThai head office or a WBC MuayThai representative their intention to defend their title before the expiration of the six-month period.20.4 Regional&nbsp;champions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">All regional champions may keep their title for a period of 6 months, with a further 2-month notification of the planned defense period. When the 6-month period expires, a regional, national, or state champion must notify the local WBC MuayThai representative of a planned defense. If no direct communication takes place from the champions team to the local WBC MuayThai representative, the WBC MuayThai, or an authorized person acting on behalf of the WBC MuayThai has the right to vacate the title without any prior written or verbal notice, 8 months from the date of a champion winning their title.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">20.5 Champions Belt/Champions Weights</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">When defending his/her WBC MuayThai belt, a champion must bring their belt to the weigh-in for publicity and bring their belt to the ring for the fight – for the duration of the fight the belt will be kept with the WBC MuayThai fight supervisor. Should a defending champion lose their title in the contest, the belt will be presented to the new champion in the ring for the purpose of publicity only; the belt will be returned to a losing champion immediately after the publicity photos are completed on the day of the fight. All new champions will receive a new belt from the WBC MuayThai within one month of winning a title. A WBC MuayThai championship promoter is responsible for purchasing a new champion’s belt.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A defending champion is not entitled to receive a new belt when they make a successful title defense; however, upon request, a promoter may purchase a new belt for a successful defending champion. However, this belt is a replica, as only when a vacant title is won on more than one occasion is a champion then recognized as a multi-time WBC MuayThai champion.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">All WBC MuayThai champions, from regional up to world champions, can only hold one WBC MuayThai title at one weight class; they can not be a champion in two weight classes simultaneously.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">20.6 Championship Appeals</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Only World title and International title contest results can be appealed through the Bangkok head office; all regional and national title contest results must be appealed through the relevant regional WBC MuayThai committee or representative. Appeals must be received within 3 days of completing a title contest with the following information attached, (a). high-definition unobstructed footage of the fight and a written reason for the appeal.<a href=\"mailto:muaythai@wbcmuaythai.com\">&nbsp;</a>All decisions by the 3-person (head office for world and International titles only) championship review committee are final. An admin fee of $500 is charged to handle the appeal, if the appeal is successful $300 will be returned. All appeals are handled through&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:muaythai@wbamuaythai.com\">muaythai@wbcmuaythai.com</a>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">20.7   Inactivity of a Champion. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Suppose a WBC Champion is or may become inactive in a manner that may prevent or unduly delay him from fulfilling his voluntary and mandatory defense obligations in the timeframe determined by the WBC on a case-by-case basis, based upon the unique facts and circumstances existing at that time in the division. In that case,&nbsp;the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;may&nbsp;declare&nbsp;the&nbsp;championship&nbsp;vacant&nbsp;and&nbsp;order&nbsp;one&nbsp;or&nbsp;more&nbsp;bouts&nbsp;to&nbsp;fill&nbsp;the&nbsp;vacant&nbsp;title.&nbsp;Such&nbsp;inactivity&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;either&nbsp;(i)&nbsp;a&nbsp;period&nbsp;of&nbsp;past&nbsp;and&nbsp;continuing&nbsp;inactivity&nbsp;or&nbsp;(ii)&nbsp;potential&nbsp;future&nbsp;inactivity&nbsp;that&nbsp;may&nbsp;prevent&nbsp;a&nbsp;champion&nbsp;from&nbsp;defending&nbsp;his&nbsp;title&nbsp;promptly,&nbsp;as&nbsp;required&nbsp;under&nbsp;these Rules.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">The&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;may&nbsp;make&nbsp;such&nbsp;a&nbsp;determination&nbsp;based&nbsp;upon&nbsp;special&nbsp;circumstances,&nbsp;which&nbsp;may include, but not be limited&nbsp;to:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<ol style=\"font-family:Rubik\" class=\"wp-block-list has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Medical issues or injury;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>legal issues or contractual impediments;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>personal or family issues; or</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Other controversies or circumstances, whether or not beyond the control of the boxer or the WBC.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">A WBC Champion’s sole responsibility is to promptly notify the WBC in writing of&nbsp;any&nbsp;circumstances&nbsp;that&nbsp;may&nbsp;prevent&nbsp;him&nbsp;from&nbsp;complying&nbsp;with&nbsp;his/her&nbsp;title&nbsp;defense obligations.&nbsp;If&nbsp;a&nbsp;champion&nbsp;fails&nbsp;to&nbsp;notify&nbsp;the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;promptly&nbsp;of such&nbsp;circumstances,&nbsp;the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;may&nbsp;take&nbsp;appropriate&nbsp;actions,&nbsp;including&nbsp;vacating&nbsp;the&nbsp;title&nbsp;or other penalties.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">20.8 Champion&nbsp;in&nbsp;Recess.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In&nbsp;certain&nbsp;cases,&nbsp;the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;MuayThai&nbsp;may,&nbsp;at&nbsp;its&nbsp;discretion,&nbsp;designate&nbsp;a&nbsp;world champion&nbsp;as&nbsp;a&nbsp;“Champion&nbsp;in&nbsp;Recess”&nbsp;if a champion can not fulfill the champion’s obligation to defend his/her title for medical reasons. Upon&nbsp;the&nbsp;boxer’s&nbsp;return,&nbsp;he/she&nbsp;will&nbsp;qualify&nbsp;to&nbsp;box&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;world&nbsp;championship&nbsp;as&nbsp;an&nbsp;elite&nbsp;contender&nbsp;to face&nbsp;the&nbsp;new&nbsp;champion.&nbsp;&nbsp;A&nbsp;Champion&nbsp;in&nbsp;Recess&nbsp;may&nbsp;return&nbsp;as&nbsp;a&nbsp;mandatory&nbsp;challenger,&nbsp;but&nbsp;only&nbsp;upon&nbsp;the&nbsp;specific&nbsp;determination&nbsp;and&nbsp;written&nbsp;approval&nbsp;of&nbsp;such&nbsp;status&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;WBC&nbsp;MuayThai,&nbsp;which may approve or deny such request in its sole discretion. The champion is Recess status has a limitation of one hundred and twenty days from the date of going into champion in recess.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">20.9 WBC MuayThai Championship Unifications&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">In accordance with the rules of The WBC MuayThai, The WBC MuayThai only host unifications contests with recognized Thai stadium titles. There are no unification bouts with any other International sanctioning body across any WBC MuayThai championship contests from national, regional and up to and including world titles. The WBC MuayThai does not interfere in the authority or activities of any other organization.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\"><strong>RULE 21: MEDICAL PROTOCOLS &amp; TIMING OF BOUT&nbsp;</strong>No fighter will be allowed to fight for a WBC MuayThai title should they lose via TKO within a 45-days of a proposed WBC MuayThai title contest and 60-days if losing via KO (suspension may be longer deeding on the severity of the KO).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">No fighter can contest for a WBC MuayThai championship contest having fought inside of 21-days before the scheduled date for a WBC MuayThai championship contest, on the grounds of safety – any fighter violating this rule automatically gives the WBC MuayThai the right to revoke sanctioning for a WBC MuayThai championship when a fighter takes a fight inside the 21-day period of contesting for a WBC MuayThai championship.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Any fighter being considered for a WBC MuayThai championship who has lost their most recent fight via KO or TKO within 90-days of the proposed date for a WBC MuayThai championship must undergo a full medical exam by a registered physician, be fully cleared by a locally registered physician (documentation of clearance to be provided to the WBC MuayThai) before any consideration is given by the WBC MuayThai to sanction a bout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Post Knockout/Technical Knockout Examinations. To protect the health and welfare of fighters, a fighter who has been knocked out (KO) or (TKO)must undergo a medical examination as quickly as possible after the bout. Such examinations should be conducted under the authority of the local combat sports commission where the bout occurred, the fighter’s local commission, or any medical authority approved by the WBC MuayThai. The following examinations should be conducted on a fighter who suffers a knockout, technical knockout, or other circumstance in which the fighter has sustained extraordinary severity of blows in a contest: a physical examination, but not limited to include a complete neurological examination, MRI/CAT Scan, or any other medical examination or tests recommended by the WBC MuayThai medical advisory board, or the attending fight physician, or local combat sports commission medical requirements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Rest Periods after Knockout. Fighters that suffered a concussion or any other serious trauma or injury by knockout should not participate in sparring sessions for a minimum of&nbsp;45 days and no less than 30 days after any other concussive trauma, including but not limited to knockout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">Suspension after Knockouts. A fighter suffering a knockout will be suspended for a minimum period of sixty (60) days. A fighter suffering two (2) consecutive knockouts will be suspended for one hundred twenty (120) days and must not be considered for a WBC MuayThai championship contest. No fighter will be allowed to fight for a WBC MuayThai title should they lose via TKO within 45-days of a proposed WBC MuayThai title contest. The minimum 60-day suspension after suffering a KO will be enforced.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontFamily\":\"Rubik\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-rubik-font-family has-custom-font\" style=\"font-family:Rubik\">WBC MuayThai titles should not be authorized or sanctioned outside of a 90-day lead in period in order to prevent inactivity of titles.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-10-21 22:30:43', '2024-10-21 22:30:43', '', 174, 'https://wbcmuaythai.com.mx/?p=244', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
